  "prompt": "How do I distinguish between different ranks of the Indian army?",
  "response": "In the Indian Army, ranks are distinguished by insignia worn on the shoulders or epaulettes of the uniform. Here's a basic overview:\n\nOfficer Ranks (from lowest to highest):\n1. Second Lieutenant\n2. Lieutenant\n3. Captain\n4. Major\n5. Lieutenant Colonel\n6. Colonel\n7. Brigadier\n8. Major General\n9. Lieutenant General\n10. General\n\nEach rank has a specific insignia:\n- Second Lieutenant: One gold star\n- Lieutenant: Two gold stars\n- Captain: Three gold stars\n- Major: One silver oak leaf\n- Lieutenant Colonel: Two silver oak leaves\n- Colonel: Silver eagle/emblem\n- Brigadier: One silver star\n- Major General: Two silver stars\n- Lieutenant General: Three silver stars\n- General: Four silver stars\n\nEnlisted ranks (from lowest to highest):\n1. Sepoy/Soldier\n2. Naik (Corporal)\n3. Havildar (Sergeant)\n4. Naib Subedar (Junior Commissioned Officer)\n5. Subedar\n6. Subedar Major\n\nEach rank has different insignia and shoulder badges indicating their position in the hierarchy.",
